---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateLink from '../components/AffiliateLink.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Webflow vs Framer: Which is Better in 2025?',
  description: 'Honest Webflow vs Framer comparison. Webflow is more powerful, Framer is easier. Which should you choose? Pricing, features, and real differences.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Webflow vs Framer', 'Webflow pricing', 'Framer pricing', 'visual website builder', 'no-code tool'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FEF9F3] py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E07A5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Tested · Honest · No Hype
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Webflow vs Framer: Which is Better?
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Webflow and Framer are the two leading visual website builders. Webflow is the established giant with more features. Framer is the modern challenger with AI and better UX. Here's how they actually compare.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: Webflow for complex sites and agencies. Framer for landing pages and designers who want faster workflow. Most people should start with Framer. Switch to Webflow only if you hit Framer's limits.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Comparison Table -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Quick Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold"><AffiliateLink href="https://webflow.com">Webflow</AffiliateLink></th>
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold"><AffiliateLink href="https://framer.com">Framer</AffiliateLink></th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border">Learning curve</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Steep (weeks to months)</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Moderate (days to weeks)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 border">AI features</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Limited</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Built-in</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border">E-commerce</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">✓ Full-featured</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">❌ No</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 border">CMS power</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">⭐⭐⭐</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border">Animation tools</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Powerful but complex</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Easy and intuitive</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 border">Community</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Huge (established)</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Growing (newer)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border">Entry price</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">$14/mo</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">$5/mo</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 border">Best for</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Complex sites, agencies</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Marketing sites, portfolios</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Pricing: Webflow vs Framer
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <!-- Webflow Pricing -->
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4"><AffiliateLink href="https://webflow.com">Webflow</AffiliateLink> Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
          <li><strong>Starter:</strong> Free (design only)</li>
          <li><strong>Basic:</strong> $14/mo (1 site)</li>
          <li><strong>CMS:</strong> $23/mo (CMS features)</li>
          <li><strong>Business:</strong> $39/mo (3 sites)</li>
          <li><strong>E-commerce:</strong> $29-212/mo</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-600">Annual billing available. No free tier for published sites.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Framer Pricing -->
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4"><AffiliateLink href="https://framer.com">Framer</AffiliateLink> Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
          <li><strong>Free:</strong> Design + publish (with branding)</li>
          <li><strong>Mini:</strong> $5/mo (1 site)</li>
          <li><strong>Plus:</strong> $15/mo (3 sites)</li>
          <li><strong>Pro:</strong> $30/mo (10 sites)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-600">Annual billing saves ~25%. No e-commerce tier.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 mt-6">
      <p class="font-black mb-2">Price winner: Framer</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Framer is cheaper at every tier. $5/mo vs $14/mo for entry level. Free tier actually publishes sites (Webflow's free is design-only). Framer's more affordable for solo creators and small projects.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Webflow Does Better -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Where Webflow Wins
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ E-commerce</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Webflow has full e-commerce features. Product catalogs, shopping cart, checkout, payments, inventory management. Framer has no e-commerce at all. If you're selling products online, Webflow wins by default.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ CMS Power</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Webflow's CMS is more powerful. Nested collections, advanced filtering, reference fields, multi-language support. Framer's CMS works for blogs and portfolios, but Webflow handles complex content architecture better.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Community and Resources</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Webflow University is incredible. Free courses, tutorials, templates, forum. Largest community of designers and developers. When you're stuck, someone has already solved it. Framer's community is growing but can't compete yet.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Enterprise Features</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Webflow has enterprise-grade features. White-labeling, advanced permissions, SSO, dedicated support. Large agencies and enterprises need these things. Framer is focused on individual creators and small teams.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Maturity and Stability</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Webflow's been around since 2012. It's battle-tested. The platform is stable. Features don't change drastically. If you're building something you need to rely on for years, Webflow's maturity matters.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Framer Does Better -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Where Framer Wins
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Learning Curve</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Framer is easier to learn. More intuitive interface. Less jargon. You'll build your first site in days, not weeks. Webflow University is great, but Webflow itself is complex. Framer gets you productive faster.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ AI Features</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Framer has built-in AI. Generate copy, create sections, build pages from prompts. Webflow has minimal AI features (mainly basic text generation). If you want AI assistance while designing, Framer is the choice.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Animations</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Framer's animation tools are easier. Add micro-interactions with clicks. Page transitions are simple. Webflow's interactions are powerful but complex. Most users only need what Framer offers.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Modern UX</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Framer feels modern. Smooth, fast, pleasant to use. Webflow's interface shows its age. Clunky in places. Feels like enterprise software. Framer feels like a modern design tool.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Speed</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Framer sites load fast. Clean code under the hood. Better performance scores out of the box. Webflow can be fast too, but requires optimization. Framer performs well by default.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Pricing</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Framer is cheaper. $5/mo vs $14/mo to start. Free tier that actually publishes. Lower cost at every tier. For budget-conscious creators, Framer wins.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who Should Choose Webflow -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Choose Webflow If:
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
        <li>• You need e-commerce features (selling products)</li>
        <li>• You're building a complex content site (magazine, resource library)</li>
        <li>• You're an agency building client sites (need white-label, enterprise features)</li>
        <li>• You want the largest community and most resources</li>
        <li>• You need advanced CMS features (nested collections, multi-language)</li>
        <li>• You're okay with a steep learning curve for more power</li>
        <li>• You need long-term stability and enterprise support</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mt-6 text-gray-700"><strong>Real example:</strong> A marketing agency building 20+ client sites per year needs Webflow's white-labeling, templates, and enterprise support. Solo freelancer building landing pages should use Framer.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who Should Choose Framer -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Choose Framer If:
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
        <li>• You're building marketing sites, landing pages, or portfolios</li>
        <li>• You want to get started fast (easier learning curve)</li>
        <li>• You like modern UX and want AI features</li>
        <li>• You don't need e-commerce or complex CMS</li>
        <li>• You're a solo creator or small team</li>
        <li>• You care about pricing and want lower monthly costs</li>
        <li>• You want easy animations and micro-interactions</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mt-6 text-gray-700"><strong>Real example:</strong> A designer building a portfolio and client landing pages should use Framer. Faster workflow, easier animations, lower cost. An e-commerce brand should use Webflow.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Smart Approach -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      The Smart Approach
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
      <p class="font-black mb-4">Start with Framer. Switch to Webflow only if you need to.</p>

      <ol class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Start your project in Framer. It's faster to learn, cheaper, and easier for most use cases.</li>

        <li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Build your site. See if Framer's features cover your needs.</li>

        <li><strong>Step 3:</strong> If you hit a limit (need e-commerce, complex CMS, enterprise features), consider migrating to Webflow.</li>

        <li><strong>Step 4:</strong> Most people never need Webflow. Framer handles 80% of use cases beautifully.</li>
      </ol>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mt-6">Switching from Framer to Webflow is easier than starting fresh. You'll have learned visual building concepts that transfer. But starting with Webflow when Framer would suffice = wasted time.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">The Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Both are excellent tools. Different strengths.</p>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li>• <strong>Webflow:</strong> Powerful, mature, e-commerce, complex CMS. Steep learning curve. Higher cost.</li>
        <li>• <strong>Framer:</strong> Easy, modern, AI features, great animations. Simpler CMS. Lower cost.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Most people should choose Framer. It's faster to learn, cheaper, and handles marketing sites beautifully. Choose Webflow only if you specifically need e-commerce or complex CMS features.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">Don't overthink it. Start with Framer. You'll know within a week if it's enough. If not, switch to Webflow. Better than spending months learning Webflow only to realize you didn't need that power.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related Comparisons
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/durable-vs-v0-vs-framer" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Durable vs v0 vs Framer</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">AI website builders compared</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/framer-ai-review" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer AI Full Review</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Deep dive on Framer</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
